# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working in this repository.

## This repo is driven by the AIDD framework in `.claude/`

This repository uses **AIDD (AI-Driven Development)** — a reusable, app-domain-agnostic delivery
framework that lives in `.claude/`. The framework itself (`.claude/skills/`, `.claude/agents/`,
`.claude/templates/`) is **the same across projects**; everything project-specific is externalized.

**Before acting, read the project layer:**
- **`.claude/PROJECT.md`** — what the product is, the stack, project-specific operating principles
  (language split, who the user is, budget authority, mock-by-default).
- **`.claude/config.json`** — machine-readable manifest (components & their lint/test/coverage checks,
  paths, vcs trailer/footer, deploy targets, enabled `domain_skills`). Scripts read this so they are
  stack-agnostic — never hardcode `pytest`/`flutter`/etc.
- **`.claude/rules/`** — `WORKFLOW.md` (the delivery-flow source of truth), `GIT.md`, `CODING.md`,
  `SECURITY.md`, `DATA_POLICY.md`, `DIRECTORY.md`, `QUALITY.md`. **Must be followed.**
- **`.claude/docs/`** — `DESIGN.md` / `SPEC.md` (entries into the larger `docs/設計書.md` /
  `docs/要件定義書.md`).

A brand-new project is bootstrapped from `.claude/templates/project/` via the **`project-init`** skill
(only PROJECT.md / config.json / docs / rules change — the framework is reused as-is).

## Universal operating principles (always — project specifics in PROJECT.md)

- **Role = PM. Decide and proceed — don't stop to confirm.** Escalate to the user **only** for
  (a) cost beyond budget, or (b) genuinely irreversible / quality-critical judgments. Everything else
  is yours to decide — act, don't ask. Don't pause on choices that don't change the outcome (ordering,
  naming, layout, equivalent approaches): pick one and continue.
- **You orchestrate and review — you do not implement directly. Delegate the work.** Hand
  design/implementation/verification/UI/content/ops work to a **sub-agent** (the `wf` workflow & its
  nodes, the specialized skills, or a direct `Agent` call), then **review what they produce** against
  the design and rules, loop back on inadequate work, and only then commit/advance. Reserve direct
  edits for your own job: `CLAUDE.md`, `.claude/` framework & rules, issue triage, orchestration glue.
- **Stopping is itself a significant decision — stopping without cause is forbidden.** When a task
  finishes: give a brief report, then immediately re-check open issues (`gh`), pick the highest-priority
  next task, and start it. Keep the loop going until there is no remaining work or you hit the
  escalation bar.
- **Routine work runs only via the scripts** — `run-checks.sh` (verify), `status.py` (ledger +
  metrics), `new-worktree.sh`/`finish-worktree.sh`, `check-content.sh`, `run-evals.sh`. Never run
  stack-specific commands ad-hoc; the scripts resolve them from `config.json`.
- **Record metrics each node** (`status.py metric`): tokens / time / loopbacks / artifacts — the
  `retro` skill uses them for the **6-criteria quality bar** and relative scoring ([rules/QUALITY.md]).
- **Commit after each unit of work.** `push` / `gh pr create` are outward-facing. **Merging into the
  default branch is the PM's decision** — the MR node only opens the PR; you check the pre-merge gate
  (CI green, no open high-severity findings, evals PASS, tree clean) and run `gh pr merge` yourself.
- **After editing any skill, run `.claude/skills/run-evals.sh`** and confirm PASS (degradation guard).
- **Questions vs. tasks.** If the user is *asking a question*, answer only — do not edit files.

## Delivery workflow & skills (`.claude/skills/`, agents in `.claude/agents/`)

Each task runs in its **own git worktree+branch per issue** (`new-worktree.sh`), with a JSON ledger at
`<work_ledger_dir>/<issue_name>/status.json` (schema `.claude/templates/status.schema.json`) updated
only via `status.py`. Overall flow, per-node mandatory checklists, the md-vs-JSON rule, the metrics
rule, the quality bar and the Skill-eval requirement: **`.claude/rules/WORKFLOW.md`**.

- **Flow nodes (generic):** `wf` (full: 設計→実装→検証→レビュー→MR, sub-agents `wf-designer` /
  `wf-implementer` / `wf-verifier` / `wf-reviewer` / `wf-mr-author`), and single nodes `wf-design` /
  `wf-implement` / `wf-verify` / `wf-review` / `wf-mr`.
- **Meta (generic):** `retro` (analyze past ledgers + metrics + PR feedback against the 6 criteria,
  improve skills/rules, validate via **blind A/B**, lock with evals — agents `retrospector` /
  `eval-judge`); `project-init` (scaffold a new project from `.claude/templates/project/`).
- **App-dev specialized (generic, domain-agnostic, stack via config):** `ui-design`, `api-design`,
  `data-migration`, `i18n`, `runtime-verify` (動作検証), `deploy`, `release`, `debug`, `refactor`, `ci`.
- **Domain plugins (project-specific, enabled in `config.domain_skills`):** `content-gen` (offline
  learning-lesson authoring — solo-leveling only).

CI runs the same checks declared in `config.json` (see `.github/workflows/ci.yml` and PROJECT.md).
